						school district or educational joint powers authority any attendance-related audit exception or exceptions involving state funds, and require the school district or educational joint powers authority to which the audit exceptions were directed to submit appropriate reporting forms for processing by the Superintendent.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) In the audit of a school district or educational joint powers authority for a subsequent year, the auditor shall review the correction or plan or plans of correction submitted by the school district or educational joint powers authority to determine if the exceptions have been resolved. If an exception has not been resolved, the auditor shall restate the exception in the audit report. After receiving a finding in an audit report, the Superintendent shall either consult with the school district or educational joint powers authority to resolve the exception or require the county superintendent of schools to follow up with the school district or educational joint powers authority.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(m) (1) (A) Each chartering authority shall be
